# ==============================================================================
# Filter Configuration Example
# ==============================================================================
# This file specifies which directories should be analyzed by clang-call-analyzer.
#
# Usage:
#   ./run.sh --filter-cfg filter.cfg
#
# Format:
#   - One filter path per line
#   - Lines starting with # are comments (ignored)
#   - Empty lines are ignored
#   - Both relative and absolute paths are supported
#   - Trailing slashes are optional (src/ == src)
#
# Path Resolution:
#   - Relative paths are resolved relative to compile_commands.json directory
#   - Absolute paths are used as-is
#
# ==============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# Main Application Source Code
# ============================================================================

# Main source directory
src/

# Include headers
include/

# Library directories
lib/
components/

# ============================================================================
# Optional: Absolute Paths
# ==============================================================================

# You can also use absolute paths if needed:
# /home/user/project/vendor/mylib/
# /opt/external/library/

# ============================================================================
# Optional: Test Files
# ============================================================================

# Include test directory if you want to analyze test code
# tests/
# test/

# ============================================================================
# Tips
# ==============================================================================
#
# 1. Start with minimal paths (just src/) and add more as needed
# 2. Use --dump-filtered-db to check what files will be analyzed
# 3. Relative paths are recommended for portability
# 4. Comments help document why certain paths are included
#
# ============================================================================
